Introduction to Research Methodology. Research methods in linguistics. Language materials and methodologies for their collection. Common methods in linguistics. Research methods in literary science. A series of seminars to discuss interim results when writing a Bachelor's thesis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1. to introduce the basics of the study to literary science and possible approaches to language and speech collection; 2. to give an overview of the methods of analysis used in modern philology; 3. to give an overview of the interpretation of the material; 4. to develop the ability to write independent research; 5. to support the process of writing a Bachelor's thesis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has finished the seminar: 1) knows the basic methods of scientific linguistic research; 2) knows and is able to collect material for linguistic research; 3) is able to apply in practice the previously acquired theoretical knowledge in planning and conducting a Bachelor's thesis; 4) is able to select and process empirical and theoretical material; 5) is able to complete the work, including references, properly.
